= Infant Feeding: Breast, Formula, or Both <ch-feeding>

== ONE-PAGE OVERVIEW

Feeding your baby is one of the most personal decisions you'll make—and one of the most debated. Here's what you need to know.

_Key Takeaways:_

1. _Breast milk provides real benefits_: Immune protection, reduced infection risk, and possible long-term health advantages for baby. For you: lower cancer and heart disease risk.

2. _Breastfeeding is natural, but not always easy_: Over 70% of mothers experience significant challenges. Only 25% manage exclusive breastfeeding for the recommended 6 months.

3. _Formula is safe, regulated nutrition_: Modern formula meets strict FDA standards for 30+ nutrients. Babies thrive on it.

4. _Support matters more than anything else_: Access to lactation consultants, peer support, and partner help dramatically improve breastfeeding outcomes.

5. _Any breast milk counts_: Combination feeding (breast milk + formula) gives your baby immune benefits while addressing practical realities.

_The Bottom Line:_ Breast milk has advantages when breastfeeding works for your family. But a well-fed baby with a healthy, supported mother is the real goal. No shame, no judgment, no martyrdom required.

